<DOC><DOCNO> SJMN91-06243251 </DOCNO><ACCESS> 06243251 </ACCESS><DESCRIPT>  WORLD; TRACK; CHAMPIONSHIP; BRIEF  </DESCRIPT><LEADPARA>  Greg Foster and Sergei Bubka shared pain, suspense and the spotlight Thursdayat the World Track and Field Championships.;   Foster, 33, overcame years ofinjuries and bad luck to win the 110-meter hurdles, but he was in suspensewhile judges determined whether he or Jack Pierce, each timed in 13.06seconds, had won.  </LEADPARA><SECTION>  Sports  </SECTION><HEADLINE>  FOSTER, BUBKA WIN STRUGGLES800 RUNNER FLOYD FAILS DRUG TEST, IS SUSPENDED  </HEADLINE><MEMO>  World Track and Field Championships  </MEMO><TEXT>     &quot;It was the lean,&quot; said Foster as he stared at a television monitor andshook his head. &quot;It looked like I started mine a little before Jack. That'swhat experience will do for you. I've been doing it for years.&quot;;   Foster wonthe event at the 1983 and 1987 World Championships, but he lost a photo-finishto Roger Kingdom at the 1984 Olympics. He was hampered by a broken arm in 1988and was halted by a collision with Canada's Mark McKoy at the 1987 WorldIndoor Championships.;   For Bubka, 27, putting recent events in the SovietUnion behind him was less difficult than relieving the misery of a sore foot.With the help of two pain-killing injections -- which are legal -- he won thepole vault by clearing 19 feet, 6 1/4 inches.;   But he had to labor. Afterclearing 18-8 1/4, he missed one attempt at 19-4 1/4, passed, then missed atthe next height, 19-6 1/4.;   He was facing a sixth-place finish if he missedhis next attempt. But just as he did in the '88 Olympics, the world-recordholder won on his final jump, clearing 19-6 1/4 and breaking the championshiprecord of 19-2 1/4 he set in 1987.; ETC.: Delisa Floyd, 30, an 800-meterrunner, was suspended for four years by the International Amateur AthleticFederation after she tested positive for an undisclosed type of amphetamines.. . . Dan O'Brien, achieved personal bests in the first three decathlon eventsand, after seven events, his 6,396 points left him 12 points off record holderDaley Thompson's pace at the 1984 Olympics.  </TEXT><BYLINE>  Mercury News Wire Services  </BYLINE><COUNTRY>  USA  </COUNTRY><CITY>  Tokyo  </CITY><EDITION>  Morning Final  </EDITION><CODE>  SJ  </CODE><NAME>  San Jose Mercury News  </NAME><PUBDATE>   910830  </PUBDATE> <DAY>  Friday  </DAY><MONTH>  August  </MONTH><PG.COL>  6D  </PG.COL><PUBYEAR>  1991  </PUBYEAR><REGION>  WEST  </REGION><STATE>  CA  </STATE><WORD.CT>  334  </WORD.CT><DATELINE>  Friday, August 30, 199100243251,SJ1  </DATELINE><COPYRGHT>  Copyright 1991, San Jose Mercury News  </COPYRGHT><LIMLEN>  1  </LIMLEN><LANGUAGE>  ENG  </LANGUAGE></DOC>